==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incarceration
<hw>In*car`cer*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>incarc⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of confining, or the state of being
confined; imprisonment.</def> <rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Formerly,
strangulation, as in hernia.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A constriction of
the hernial sac, rendering it irreducible, but not great enough to cause
strangulation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incarcerator</ent>⟦br⟧
